In the limit $n \gg l$, we use an asymptotic expression for the binomial coefficient to obtain

\begin{eqnarray}
\binom{n}{l} \left( \frac{|\alpha_{k}|}{\mu} \right)^{n} &=& \binom{n}{l} \mathrm{e}^{-n \ln{(\mu/|\alpha_{k}|)}} \nonumber \\
&\simeq & \frac{(n/l - 1/2)^{l}\,\mathrm{e}^{l}}{\sqrt{2\pi\,l}}\,\mathrm{e}^{-n \ln{(\mu/|\alpha_{k}|)}} \nonumber \\
& < & n^{l}\,\mathrm{e}^{-n \ln{(\mu/|\alpha_{k}|)}}\,.
\label{ap9}
\end{eqnarray}

